Redesign the portfolio UI with the following design direction:

---

## Overall Concept
- Theme: Creative & distinctive — not a generic developer template
- Must stand out from typical portfolio sites while still feeling professional
- Dark / Light mode toggle supported (default: Dark)

---

## Visual Style
- Bold typography with intentional font size contrast (large hero text, small labels)
- Asymmetric layouts where appropriate — avoid boring centered-everything grids
- Subtle but satisfying micro-interactions (hover effects, scroll-triggered animations)
- Use Framer Motion for entrance animations per section
- Cursor custom effect or subtle interactive element on hero section

---

## Color System
### Dark Mode
- Background: near-black (#0a0a0a or #0f0f0f)
- Primary accent: electric indigo or violet (#6366f1 or similar)
- Secondary accent: soft cyan or mint for contrast
- Text: off-white (#f0f0f0), muted gray for secondary text

### Light Mode
- Background: warm off-white (#fafaf9)
- Same accent colors, slightly deeper
- Text: deep charcoal (#1a1a1a)

---

## Typography
- Hero heading: 80–96px, bold or black weight, tight letter-spacing
- Use a modern sans-serif (e.g. Inter, Geist, or Sora via Google Fonts)
- Section titles: large, with a thin decorative line or number prefix (e.g. "01. About")
- Body text: 16px, comfortable line-height (1.7)

---

## Layout Details
### Hero Section
- Full viewport height
- Large name text with a subtle gradient or glitch/shimmer effect
- Animated role text (typewriter or word-swap animation)
- Floating abstract shape or grid pattern in background (CSS or canvas — keep it light)
- CTA buttons: outlined style, hover fills with accent color

### Skills Section
- Skill badges with icons, grouped by category
- Hover reveals proficiency or short note

### Projects Section
- Large cards with image/mockup placeholder
- Card hover: slight lift + accent border glow
- Tag chips for tech stack

### Experience Section
- Vertical timeline with accent-colored dots and connecting line
- Each entry slides in on scroll

---

## Do's and Don'ts
✅ Use CSS variables for all colors (easy theme switching)
✅ Smooth scroll, section transitions
✅ Mobile-first responsive
✅ Clean component structure (one component per section)
❌ No stock photo backgrounds
❌ No rainbow/excessive color use
❌ No heavy JS libraries beyond Framer Motion
❌ Don't make it look like every other Tailwind portfolio

---

## Implementation Notes
- Tailwind CSS with custom theme extension for colors
- next-themes for dark/light toggle
- Framer Motion for all animations
- Keep bundle size lean